Ecology.Usages:
* Due to their abundance in the region, rabbits were a common source of food in the Dalelands.
* It was quite common for inns of average quality in the Realms to serve rabbit meat as the third part of a four-course meal.<ref>{{Cite web/theedverse/Four-course meals of the Realms}}
* [[The Black Horse]] in [[Archenbridge]] often served pies with rabbit meat as filling.
* The [[High Flagon]] in [[Waterdeep]] offered its patrons savory [[tart]]s filled with small game, such as rabbits.{{Cite dragon/302/Elminster's Guide to the Realms: The High Flagon|77}}
* In [[Neverwinter]], some impoverished folk were known to bake savory pies with rabbit meat as a filling.<ref>{{Cite web/theedverse/2019-11-26 - Neverwinter Cuisine}}
